    <abstract>
      <t>This informational document gives examples of SIP (Session Initiation
Protocol) call flows for IP telephony.  Elements in these call flows
include SIP User Agents and Clients, SIP Proxy and Redirect Servers,
and Gateways to the PSTN (Public Switch Telephone Network).</t>
